review_text: I visited this daycare for an assessment. Although my puppy wasnt suitable at the moment (she was too anxious and overwhelmed by the new environment as she had never been to one before), I was impressed by the exceptional professionalism and care provided by Christine, the owner. She took the time to thoroughly assess each dog before admitting them into the daycare and also provided valuable advice on how to better prepare my dog for this type of environment. I truly appreciate her sincerity and expertise. Hope to come back in the near future when my pups ready!

Been using the groomer here for a couple of months, very happy with the cuts. AFAIK they only work on 1 dog at a time, so if your little one doesnt like chaos this should be a great option. (The doggie day care is downstairs, away from the groomer station.)

Our dog has been coming to daycare for over a year every day and he loves it!  Everyone is kind and cares about the owners and the dogs.  Have been recommending them to others as a great place to let your dog enjoy their day and not worry about them being bored or lonely!

I LOVE this place and so does my pup! Weve taken a couple of obedience classes here as well as some agility. Christine is a really great trainer, she uses a lot of positive reinforcement techniques. The daycare is great, my pup goes 1-2 times a week. There is always someone there watching them. My pup gets so tired that on the way home she cant even stay awake while sitting up! All the staff are super friendly too. I highly recommend this place!

great full service place!! Daycare to run off the steam of a little puppy, training to help focus that steam as the puppy grows up, and grooming for when the steam gets to be a little too much. Christine runs a great place, all 3 of my dogs go there, with the pup being the regular. 2x week for daycare and consecutive training classes, excellent followup by emails for any issues, questions, help with those issues that you always have with a puppy or new dog. Kristy and Yoshika are excellent groomers and my dogs love them. Check them out on facebook - pics of the doggies at daycare! great friendly staff and always accommodating, no matter what you need!

This is a pretty small operation, so they cant always pick up the phone, especially if theyre looking after lots of dogs. Theyre very pleasant and great with the dogs and to top it off their prices are quite reasonable. Id definitely recommend them for anyone looking for a great daycare or for grooming, just dont forget that its a small operation and they cant always pick up the phone :)

Downtown Dogs is a great space to bring your pooch. We took our puppy in for obedience training classes, and he is now the most obedient dog we have met. We cant wait for the next set of classes - thanks again, Christine!
Just took my little 4 pound dog here!! They were very welcoming and gentle with my dog. Nails are cut good and it was very quick!! Vet was $17 this place is $10.50!! Love it, will be back.
Took our newly adopted dog here to get his nails clipped. Professional and speedy service as well as genuine care for animals. Will definitely be returning in the future.
Excellent place, good service, very nice people. Our dog graduate from that training school. Our favorite place for our hairy son.
The groomers do amazing work on my cats and dog plus the daycare all the dog have so much fun and come out happy its a great I recommend this place for sure
Calm friendly environment, professional groomers, reasonable price.

Not great - bit of a dump and no place for the dogs to run..  Seemed to be piled on top of one another.  Wouldnt leave my dog there. Grooming was ok, would probably take him there again if I didnt have another choice.  Now Im looking around, this would not be my first choice.
response_from_owner_text: Hi June, thank you for your feedback. I assume you used only our grooming services (our daycare is not visible from the front of our business), however going back I am unable to find a record of your visit to us. Please contact me directly if you would like to discuss your experience further. Thank you!
